article.headline: Northern Arizona 84, San Francisco 62
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Stephen Sir scored 20 points while Tyrone Bazy and Ruben Boykin Jr. each added 18 as Northern Arizona beat San Francisco 84-62 Tuesday night. Josh Wilson finished with 13 points for the Lumberjacks (4-4), who led 51-30 at halftime and were never threatened from there. Ryan McCurdy pulled down 12 rebounds for NAU and Boykin had 10 boards. San Francisco (4-6) was paced by Antonio Kellogg's 13 points while Armondo Surratt added 11.
